title._content: Women in Church Vocations study conference 1957

description._content:
2013-0127m
"Members of St. Louis Study Commission on Women in church vocations sponsored by the General Conference Board of Christian Service. From left, Cornelia Lehn, Justina Neufeld, Elma Esau, Esther Unruh, Marvin Ewert, Ralph Weber, Carolyn Schnell, Elmer Ediger, Margaret Voth, Mrs. Edith Graber, Doreen Harms, and Onale Stucky. In addition Pastor Krantz, and Evelyn Middelstadt, president of the Lutheran group with whom the commission met for several sessions."
Photographer: Elmer O. Konradi, St. Louis, Missouri
Mennonite Publication Office cut no. 12419
used in Mennonite Life, Jan. 1957, p. 42
